{"lemma": "مُعَقِّبٌ", "slug": "مُعَقِّبٌ", "root": "ع.ق.ب", "root_slug": "ع-ق-ب", "root_link": "/words/roots/ع-ق-ب", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "مُعَقِّب", "root": "عقب", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 1}, "wiktextract": {"found": false}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n29860"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%91%D8%A8%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "successor angel", "fa": "فرشته پیرو", "ur": "پیچھے آنے والا فرشتہ", "tr": "takip eden melek", "id": "malaikat pengganti", "bn": "পরবর্তী ফেরেশতা", "es": "ángel sucesor", "fr": "ange successeur", "de": "nachfolgender Engel", "ru": "ангел-преемник", "zh": "继任天使"}, "definition": null, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n29860", "headword_ar": "مُعَقِّبٌ", "root": "Eqb", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Coming after,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "near after, another thing."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O.) See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaqiybN", "text_ar": "عَقِيبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b2-  It is said that it is applied as an epithet to an angel; that one says"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "malaka muEaq~ibN", "text_ar": "مَلَكَ مُعَقِّبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "An angel that follows another"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "malaAy^ikapN muEaq~ibapN", "text_ar": "مَلَايِكَةٌ مُعَقِّبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muEaq~ibaAtN", "text_ar": "مُعَقِّبَاتٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a pl. pl. (O.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmuEaq~ibaAtu", "text_ar": "المُعَقِّبَاتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The angels of the night and the day;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, K;) because they succeed one another by turns; and the fem. form is used because of the frequency of their doing so, in like manner as it is in the words"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nas~aAbapN", "text_ar": "نَسَّابَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eal~aAmapN", "text_ar": "عَلَّامَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S, O:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the angles called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHafaZapu", "text_ar": "الحَفَظَةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAfiZN", "text_ar": "حَافِظٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v.]: so in the Kur xiii. 12: in which some of the Arabs of the desert read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maEaAqiybu", "text_ar": "مَعَاقِيبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) this [may be an anomalous pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaqiybN", "text_ar": "عَقِيبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mahaAjiynu", "text_ar": "مَهَاجِينُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "hajiynN", "text_ar": "هَجِينٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or it] is pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muEaq~ibN", "text_ar": "مُعَقِّبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muEaq~ibapN", "text_ar": "مُعَقِّبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being to compensate for the suppression of one of the two"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "q", "text_ar": "ق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Bd.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmuEaq~ibaAtu", "text_ar": "المُعَقِّبَاتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The she-camels that stand behind those that are pressing towards the wateringtrough,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "tank; so that when one she-camel goes away, another comes in her place."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, K.) ―         -b4-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The ejaculations of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suboHaAna A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "سُبْحَانَ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which follow"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2104}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one another,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "repeated at the end of the ordinary prayer, thirty-three in number, and which are followed by"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AaloHamodu lil~`hi", "text_ar": "اَلْحَمْدُ لِلّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thirty-three times, and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aall~`hu A^akobaro", "text_ar": "اَللّٰهُ اَكْبَرْ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thirty-four times."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O.) ―         -b5-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muEaq~ibN", "text_ar": "مُعَقِّبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies also One"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who makes repeatedly warring,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "warring and plundering, expeditions;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who journeys repeatedly, and does not stay with his family after his return."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b6-  And One"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who seeks after a thing repeatedly, striving,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "exerting himself:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O:) one"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who follows after a thing that is his due, demanding restitution of it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or one"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who follows close after a man, for something that is his due:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "one"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who seeks to recover his right,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "due:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and one"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who, being despoiled of all his property in a hostile attack, makes a hostile attack upon him from whom he has thus suffered, and endeavours to recover his property."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) Lebeed says, describing a [wild] he-ass and his female,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "Hat~aY tahaj~ara biAlr~awaAHi wahaAjahaA\n                      \n                     \n                        Talaba AlmuEaq~ibi Haq~ahu AlmuZoluwmu"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, but in the latter"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY Alr~awaAHi", "text_ar": "فِى الرَّوَاحِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) i. e. ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Until he went along in the midday heat,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bAlrwAH", "text_ar": "بالرواح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fY", "text_ar": "فى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlrwAH", "text_ar": "الرواح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being redundant,)]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and drove her on"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[by a pursuit]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "like the seeking of him who is making repeated efforts, having been wronged, to obtain his due:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(O:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmZlwm", "text_ar": "المظلوم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is an epithet qualifying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmEq~b", "text_ar": "المعقّب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and is in the nom. case agreeable with the meaning, (S, O,) because it is put after its proper place; (O;) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmEq~b", "text_ar": "المعقّب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is literally in the gen. case, but as to the meaning is an agent: (S, O: *) or, accord. to some,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmEq~b", "text_ar": "المعقّب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[here] signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the debtor who puts off the payment of his debt;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmZlwm", "text_ar": "المظلوم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is an agent and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmEq~b", "text_ar": "المعقّب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is an objective complement: (S:) or, as some say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlmEq~b", "text_ar": "المعقّب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he who demands the payment of a debt and repeats his demand thereof."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b7-  Also Any one"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "returning"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[app. to the doing of a thing]. (O.) ―         -b8-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maEaAqibN", "text_ar": "مَعَاقِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b9-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA muEaq~iba liHukomihi", "text_ar": "لَا مُعَقِّبَ لِحُكْمِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the Kur [xiii. 41], means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "There is no repeller of his decree."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)       -A2-  Also A man"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who descends into a well to raise a stone of the kind called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EuqaAb", "text_ar": "عُقَاب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) [See also the verb.]"}], "source_refs": ["S", "O", "TA", "K"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}